<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,577,1180]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,973,999]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Biology and notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bigot" authorityYear="1882" box="[427,603,973,999]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Tropidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notata">
<emphasis box="[427,603,973,999]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Tropidia notata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with the highlands of the Chilean Andes. Mining operations are probably the main threat for this flower fly. In 
<collectingCountry box="[704,818,1009,1035]" name="Argentina" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, this species has been associated with the Andean shrub 
<taxonomicName authority="(Clos) Benth. &amp; Hook. ex Weberb (Medan 2003)" authorityName="Benth. &amp; Hook. ex Weberb (Medan" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Clos" box="[151,881,1045,1072]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Discaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nana">
